cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper involves the use of a biological organism to imitate the development of man-made transport networks, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). It also involves the analysis of data and the extraction of topologies, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of 3D terrains and the role of elevations in shaping human movement networks suggest the involvement of computer graphics and computer-aided design (cs.CE) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of a biological organism to imitate human migration routes could also fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
